productTitle: Air Filter Factory Replacement For Essick Air MA1201, MA-1201 Humidifier Wick Filter
text: I’ve been getting these as a recurring order for years now. What I like about this particular one is that there’s an aluminum band woven into the fabric that helps it keep its shape. It lasts just shy of a month if you have dirty water. It can quickly soak water and get humidity into a large room. Mine is around 500sqft and not well insulated. It’s the second story of a garage that I finished with drywall, flooring, and windows but it’s still not as solid as a house so it can get leaky and let in some drafts and allow dry air in. This filter is great for quickly soaking the water up and getting the air feeling good again. Remember to actually roll it backward when you get it. It’ll come folded one way. You need to unfold it the exact opposite way when installing so that it feels like it wants to bend back into its original shape but cannot. This is what helps it keep its shape. What I do is once I get it installed in the humidifier I take a piece of the metal band and sort of use it like a twist tie to hold the two ends together so it stays in place. It fits perfectly in the humidifier. After some time the water will oxidize the metal bands at the top and bottom (there’s only two thin ones) and leave you with these sort of gray crumbs. Don’t be alarmed. That’s normal and just oxidized metal that came off. I try to wash out the basin of the humidifier every 3 months to get rid of that stuff but generally skip it in the winter because it’s too cold out to hose the thing down. But yeah, I love this product and hope they never stop making it.
date: Reviewed in the United States on December 19, 2024
title: Stick with the name brand

productTitle: Air Filter Factory Replacement For Essick Air MA1201, MA-1201 Humidifier Wick Filter
text: I have been ordering these filters for years. The metal in them really helps them hold their shape. I have found that adding the Best Air Humidifier 3 Step Treatment works really good. To help the longevity I turn the filter over about every three days. This really helps the filter last longer. We burn a fireplace which really takes the humidity out of the air. I usually order 3 filters which last from about November - March. By turning the filter over it gives the treatment a better chance to dissolve the crusty layer from the top and puts a fresher moist top to the filter. I usually get about a month and a half to 2 months out of a filter with the humidifier running all the time. It is also important to keep the humidifier full of water.
